    <h2 id="dependency-analysis">Dependency Analysis</h2>

    <div style="background: var(--bg-secondary, #f5f5f5); padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <h3>Execution Dependencies</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>G.1 (SQL Injection) is PREREQUISITE</strong> for testing framework - must fix first</li>
            <li><strong>G.2 (Command Injection) is INDEPENDENT</strong> - can run in parallel with G.1</li>
            <li><strong>G.3 (Password Hashing) is INDEPENDENT</strong> - can run in parallel but needs DB schema update before deployment</li>
            <li><strong>G.4 (Session/CSRF) has SOFT DEPENDENCY</strong> on G.1 for testing but can be developed in parallel</li>
            <li><strong>G.5 (Encryption) is INDEPENDENT</strong> - can run entirely in parallel with other fixes</li>
            <li><strong>G.6 (Input Validation/Headers) is INDEPENDENT</strong> - can run in parallel but should be after high-severity fixes</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Optimal Execution Sequence:</strong> G.1 first (CRITICAL), then parallel tracks: (G.2 + G.3 + G.4) in parallel with G.5, then G.6 last</p>
    </div>

